            "body": "<p>Why are you trying to reinvent the wheel? Use an <code>ArrayList<\/code> instead as this can give you the index of an element in the list:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\n\n// add elements\nlist.add(\"first\");\nlist.add(\"second\");\n\n// get index of an element\nlist.indexOf(\"second\");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
